rComments: Peter Kuling is a great guy and a great prof. The textbook for this class (Cambridge intro to theatre studies) absolutely sucks and is super hard to get through, but if you go to the lectures and ask questions it's honestly so easy to do well. He also picks great plays to read

Took this class hoping it would be an easy A+, but getting an A+ in business or economics is way easier and takes less effort. He lied at the beginning of the year by saying the final exam would be a take-home asking us questions about an event. It turns out it was a 10-page essay! Just take an easier course that looks better on your transcript.
This professor is very kind and has really good lectures but he is very slow on marking.

Peter Kuling is definitely the best professor in the theatre department, and maybe the whole university. He is passionate and makes his classes as exciting as he can, often showing videos or allowing discussions. He seems to genuinely care about his students. He is very socially aware, always respectful of everyone's personal situations, PC. Great!

Dr. Kuling is the best professor this university will ever have. He is fair but he still challenges his students. He wants his students to succeed but he wants them to learn. He's hilarious and has the funniest ideas but he still conveys the course material effectively.

Stimulating and unique take on theatre and the performing arts, made me think a lot about what it means to be a performer and consume performances. Very understanding of any situation, and also will give you great feedback to everything. Very easy to approach.

Literally such a pleasure to have as a prof. His teaching is incredibly stimulating, and he makes the somewhat dry material very attainable and enjoyable. One midterm, One final, one paper, and participation marks (/10).

A really fun professor, had some really cool components to the class (like playing games on Twitch and going to Red Bull Crashed Ice). Very clear expectations and grading, no textbook or reading to do, just going to events and shows and writing about them.
It's an easy A class, but also a FUN A class. His lectures are great.
